## Complete New Subnet Design

### VPC-A (10.0.0.0/16) — Cloud Host / Management

```
subnet-a-public    10.0.1.0/24   PUBLIC
  Hosts: A1 Windows (10.0.1.10), A2 Linux (10.0.1.20), NAT Gateway
  IGW: igw-a (existing)
  Route table:
    10.0.0.0/16 → local
    10.1.0.0/16 → TGW1
    10.2.0.0/16 → TGW1
    0.0.0.0/0   → IGW (for A1/A2 public internet)
    [TGW1 brings traffic from B/C/D destined for NAT GW]
    → NAT GW → IGW handles that via VPC-A route table
```

No subnet changes in VPC-A. NAT Gateway and EIP are new resources here.

-----

### VPC-B (10.1.0.0/16) — Palo Alto NGFW

```
subnet-b-untrust   10.1.1.0/24   PUBLIC
  Hosts: Palo UNTRUST ENI (10.1.1.10), ALB, NLB-B
  IGW: igw-b (NEW — VPC-B needs its own IGW for internet-facing untrust)
  Route table:
    10.1.0.0/16 → local
    0.0.0.0/0   → igw-b

subnet-b-trust     10.1.2.0/24   PRIVATE
  Hosts: Palo TRUST ENI (10.1.2.10)
  Route table:
    10.1.0.0/16 → local
    10.0.0.0/16 → TGW1  (return to mgmt)
    10.2.0.0/16 → TGW1  (toward AppGate)
    10.3.0.0/16 → TGW2  (return to customer sim VPC-D)
    0.0.0.0/0   → TGW1  (centralized egress via VPC-A NAT GW)

subnet-b-mgmt      10.1.3.0/24   PRIVATE
  Hosts: Palo MGMT ENI (10.1.3.10)
  Route table:
    10.1.0.0/16 → local
    10.0.0.0/16 → TGW1  (reachable from VPC-A management)
    0.0.0.0/0   → TGW1  (centralized egress for Panorama/updates)
```

VPC-B needs a NEW Internet Gateway (igw-b) attached to VPC-B.
Only subnet-b-untrust uses it. Trust and mgmt subnets have no IGW route.

