## Palo Alto ENI Configuration (CRITICAL)

B1 simulates the Palo Alto VM-Series NGFW. In production this is a
licensed VM-Series appliance. In the lab it is an EC2 instance with
three separate ENIs simulating the three Palo data/mgmt planes.

### ENI Resources — Create as STANDALONE aws_network_interface resources

Do NOT define ENIs inline in the instance resource block.
Standalone ENIs allow source_dest_check to be set at the ENI level.

```hcl
resource "aws_network_interface" "palo_untrust" {
  subnet_id         = aws_subnet.subnet_b_untrust.id
  private_ips       = ["10.1.1.10"]
  source_dest_check = false   # MANDATORY — Palo routes others' traffic
  security_groups   = [aws_security_group.sg_palo_untrust.id]
  tags = { Name = "palo-eni-untrust" }
}

resource "aws_network_interface" "palo_trust" {
  subnet_id         = aws_subnet.subnet_b_trust.id
  private_ips       = ["10.1.2.10"]
  source_dest_check = false   # MANDATORY
  security_groups   = [aws_security_group.sg_palo_trust.id]
  tags = { Name = "palo-eni-trust" }
}

resource "aws_network_interface" "palo_mgmt" {
  subnet_id         = aws_subnet.subnet_b_mgmt.id
  private_ips       = ["10.1.3.10"]
  source_dest_check = true    # MGMT ENI is destination — check stays on
  security_groups   = [aws_security_group.sg_palo_mgmt.id]
  tags = { Name = "palo-eni-mgmt" }
}
```

### ENI Attachment to B1 Instance

device_index ordering is fixed — do not change:

- device_index = 0 → UNTRUST (eth0) — primary interface
- device_index = 1 → TRUST (eth1)
- device_index = 2 → MGMT (eth2)

```hcl
resource "aws_instance" "b1" {
  ami           = data.aws_ami.al2023.id
  instance_type = "t3.medium"   # needs more RAM for multi-ENI
  # Do NOT specify subnet_id here — ENIs control placement

  network_interface {
    network_interface_id = aws_network_interface.palo_untrust.id
    device_index         = 0
  }
  network_interface {
    network_interface_id = aws_network_interface.palo_trust.id
    device_index         = 1
  }
  network_interface {
    network_interface_id = aws_network_interface.palo_mgmt.id
    device_index         = 2
  }
}
```

### EIP for UNTRUST ENI

```hcl
resource "aws_eip" "palo_untrust_eip" {
  domain                    = "vpc"
  network_interface         = aws_network_interface.palo_untrust.id
  associate_with_private_ip = "10.1.1.10"
  depends_on                = [aws_internet_gateway.igw_b]
}
```

