## ALB — Internet-Facing Customer Entry Point

```
Placement:   subnet-b-untrust (10.1.1.0/24), VPC-B
Type:        application (layer 7)
Scheme:      internet-facing
Listener:    HTTPS 443 with ACM certificate
Target:      Palo UNTRUST ENI (10.1.1.10) port 443
```

Security Group on ALB:

- Ingress: TCP 443 from 0.0.0.0/0 (customers from internet)
- Ingress: TCP 80 from 0.0.0.0/0 (redirect to 443)
- Egress: TCP 443 to 10.1.1.0/24 (toward Palo untrust ENI)

This is the ONLY internet-facing resource in the customer traffic path.

