## NAT Gateway — Centralized Management Egress

```
Placement:   subnet-a-public (10.0.1.0/24), VPC-A
Requires:    Elastic IP
```

This is NOT in the customer traffic path.
Used only for: OS updates, AppGate license checks, Panorama calls,
IdP federation calls, yum/dnf package installs on private instances.

Customer traffic enters through ALB → Palo and exits through
Palo UNTRUST ENI → ALB → IGW. Never touches VPC-A or NAT GW.

Cloud Host (VPC-A) billing/SLA visibility is handled by VPC Flow Logs
on VPC-A forwarded to CloudWatch — NOT by routing customer traffic
through VPC-A. This satisfies the cloud host’s operational support
requirement without adding any hop to the customer path.

```hcl
resource "aws_eip" "nat_gw_eip" {
  domain     = "vpc"
  depends_on = [aws_internet_gateway.igw_a]
}

resource "aws_nat_gateway" "nat_gw_a" {
  allocation_id = aws_eip.nat_gw_eip.id
  subnet_id     = aws_subnet.subnet_a_public.id
  depends_on    = [aws_internet_gateway.igw_a]
  tags = { Name = "nat-gw-vpc-a-centralized-egress" }
}
```

