## What You Must NOT Do

- Do not give any public IP to B1 trust/mgmt ENIs, C1, or D1
- Do not add an IGW to VPC-C or VPC-D — they have no internet-facing resources
- Do not make NLB-B or NLB-C internet-facing (scheme must be internal)
- Do not define Palo ENIs inline in the instance block — use standalone resources
- Do not set source_dest_check = false on the MGMT ENI — only untrust and trust
- Do not put the NAT Gateway in VPC-B, C, or D
- Do not route customer traffic through VPC-A — NAT GW is management egress only
- Do not add a route from VPC-D to VPC-A — management isolation must hold
- Do not add VPC peering between any VPCs — all routing goes through TGW
- Do not skip terraform plan review — B1 and C1 will be destroyed/recreated
- Do not apply if terraform plan shows unexpected destroys beyond B1 and C1

