## ADDENDUM: AppGate Stack Instances (Controller, Gateway, Portal)

VPC-C must have three separate EC2 instances simulating the real AppGate
SDP collective. The previous single C1 instance is replaced by three
purpose-specific instances, each in its correct subnet with the correct
ports, roles, and HTML page identifying what it simulates.

-----

### AppGate Collective — Role Reference

|Appliance |Role                                |Real Function                                                                                                                                  |
|----------|------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Controller|Policy Administrator + Policy Engine|Authenticates users, evaluates entitlements, issues session tokens. Admin UI on port 8443. Peer port 444. Never directly in customer data path.|
|Gateway   |Policy Enforcement Point            |Enforces per-user micro-tunnels. All customer data traffic flows through here. Port 443 (tunnel).                                              |
|Portal    |Clientless Browser Access           |Receives customer browser sessions. Performs SPA on behalf of browser users. Port 443 (HTTPS). Fronted by NLB-C.                               |

The AppGate SDP Controller offers Policy Administrator and Policy Engine functionality, while Gateways act as the Policy Enforcement Point.
The controller admin interface runs on port 8443, or port 444 if using the peer interface.

